  "text": "Mechanisms to monitor hit information have been described by many researchers [CITATION_1] . Similar to UMON , E-UMON monitors hit information of an application executing on core c through a shadow tag array and hit counters. The shadow tag array has the same associativity as the shared LLC. Each shadow tag entry has three fields: valid bit (V), tag address (TAG), and LRU bits (LRU) that track stack distance of each access. Dynamic set sampling ] is applied to reduce the hardware overhead. Our evaluation shows that sampling 32 sets is sufficient for a cache with 2048 sets.",
